  "body": "Given that [React does attach event handlers to the nodes themselves](https://github.com/facebook/react/issues/13625), does the React team recommend app developers to do event delegation when working with large lists for saving memory? Something like:\r\n\r\n```jsx\r\nimport React from 'react';\r\nimport ReactDOM from 'react-dom';\r\n\r\nclass App extends React.Component {\r\n  render() {\r\n    return (\r\n      <ul onClick={(e) => console.log(`ID: ${e.target.dataset.id} was clicked`)}>\r\n        <li data-id=\"1\">Item 1</li>\r\n        <li data-id=\"2\">Item 2</li>\r\n        <li data-id=\"3\">Item 3</li>\r\n        ...\r\n      </ul>\r\n    );\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\nReactDOM.render(<App />, document.getElementById('root'));\r\n```",
